'''Free action''' is a [[property]] in ''[[NetHack]]'' that protects you from many sources of [[paralysis]]. This property is distinct from "free actions" that [[you]] can take without incrementing the [[turn]] counter, as well as the additional movement points that you or a monster can gain with [[speed]].

The only source of the free action property is the [[ring of free action]].

{{upcoming|3.7.0|[[Orange dragon scales]] and orange-scaled mail now also grant free action when worn, derived from variants like [[dNetHack]] and [[FIQHack]].}}

==Description==
Free action nullifies or blunts the effects of the following:

* Paralayzing [[container trap]]s will have no effect.{{refsrc|src/trap.c|4945|version=NetHack 3.6.7}}
* [[Thrown]] or [[quaff]]ed [[potion]]s of {{! of|paralysis|or=1|sleeping}} and their [[vapor]]s will have no effect.{{refsrc|src/potion.c|792|version=NetHack 3.6.7}}{{refsrc|src/potion.c|807|version=NetHack 3.6.7}}{{refsrc|src/potion.c|1716|version=NetHack 3.6.7}}{{refsrc|src/potion.c|1727|version=NetHack 3.6.7}}
* The [[Paralyze (monster spell)|paralyze]] and [[Stun (monster spell)|stun]] [[monster spell]]s will only affect you for 1 turn.{{refsrc|src/mcastu.c|475|version=NetHack 3.6.7}}{{refsrc|src/mcastu.c|671|version=NetHack 3.6.7}}
* Paralyzing [[Damage type|attacks]] from the following sources:{{refsrc|src/mhitu.c|1181|version=NetHack 3.6.7}}
** The passive gaze of a [[floating eye]]{{refsrc|src/uhitm.c|2893|version=NetHack 3.6.7|name="hiteye"}}{{refsrc|src/polyself.c|1429|version=NetHack 3.6.7|name="polyeye"|comment=Using a gaze attack against a floating eye while polymorphed}}
** The passive and touch attacks of a [[gelatinous cube]]
** The claw attacks of [[ghoul]]s and [[Yeenoghu]]
** The bite of a [[guardian naga]]
** The touch attack of a [[shade]]

Free action does ''not'' protect you from:

* Being "paralyzed" by fear, e.g. from encountering a [[ghost]] or [[chat]]ting to a [[skeleton]]
* 'Paralysis' by [[lightning]] in clouds on the [[Plane of Air]]{{refsrc|src/timeout.c|1613|nethack=3.6.7}}
* Immobility induced by various other items, properties and elements (e.g., [[fumbling]] or using the [[Turn (command)|#turn]] [[extended command]])

==Strategy==
Free action is often considered essential, especially for endgame areas such as [[Moloch's Sanctum]] and the [[Astral Plane]]. A thrown potion of paralysis can easily result in your death if one hits you in the midst of a pitched battle, and hostile [[aligned priest]]s can end your run with a single ill-timed paralyze spell.

Players often combine a ring of free action with a wielded potion of paralysis to immobilize and dispose of difficult (and usually [[covetous]]) monsters with much less risk to themselves. Some will [[wish]] or [[polypile]] for a ring of free action if they have not found one by the time they are ready to take on the [[Wizard of Yendor]] and perform the [[Invocation]].

Despite its usefulness, it is very possible to ascend without a source of free action, as most forms paralysis outside of the potion can be compensated for with other precautions: monsters with paralyzing attacks and spells can be kept out of melee range, and items such as a [[ring of conflict]] and/or an [[amulet of life saving]] can be useful in a pinch.

{{upcoming|3.7.0|[[Orange dragon scales]] and orange-scaled mail grant free action as well as [[sleep resistance]] when worn, making the property more accessible without the ring.}}

