{{message|You stiffen briefly.|Free action prevented the paralyze monster spell from paralyzing you.}}

==Variants==
===SLASH'EM===
In [[SLASH'EM]], free action also protects against [[holding attack]]s, including drowning grab attacks and [[mind flayer]] tentacle attacks (which are reclassified as holding attacks). The chance is dependent on your [[Luck]], ranging from a {{frac|2}} chance at 0 Luck to {{frac|9|10}} at maximum Luck.

====Messages====
{{message|<foo> grabs you, but you quickly free yourself!|Free action prevented a monster from grabbing you with a holding attack.}}

===NetHack brass===
In [[NetHack brass]], orange dragon scale mail also provides free action alongside its [[sleep resistance]].

===dNetHack===
In [[dNetHack]], free action also extends the amount of turns that a player has to act while [[Stoning|turning to stone]].

Orange dragon scales and scaled armor provide free action alongside sleep resistance, and [[The Iron Spoon of Liberation]] provides free action when carried.

[[Spirits (dNetHack)#Eurynome, the Lonely Dancer|Eurynome, the Lonely Dancer]] is a spirit that grants free action.

===FIQHack===
In [[FIQHack]], free action prevents you or a monster from being subjected to slowing effects (e.g. the [[wand of slow monster]]) {{frac|2|3}} of the time. Orange dragon scales and scale mail provide free action alongside sleep resistance, and [[Snickersnee]] also provides free action.

Free action is one of the properties that can be granted by quaffing or dipping into a [[potion of wonder]].

===EvilHack===
In [[EvilHack]], the [[shield of mobility]] provides free action while worn, and monsters will wear both the shield and the ring of free action if possible; monster AI will give magic resistance and reflection priority over free action.

